I’ve implemented the enhancements so your complex G2 example is supported.

What’s supported now
- Data fetch: pass data as { type: "fetch", value: "https://..." }.
- Top-level transforms: stackY with orderBy, reverse, offset, y (custom output channel).
- Child transforms: children can have their own transform array (e.g., stackY with y: 'y1').
- Function-like encoders for children: encode.x and encode.y can be function strings like "(d) => new Date(d.year)" (embedded as executable code).
- Series/color/shape encoders and mark-level style/tooltip supported in children.

Changes made
- src/charts/area.ts
  - TransformSchema: added reverse?: boolean and y?: string.
  - ChildMarkSchema: added transform?: TransformSchema so children can specify transforms.
  - Data union already supports common shapes and arbitrary records when encode is present.
- src/renderer/builders/g2/area.ts
  - buildTransforms: passes through reverse and y for stackY.
  - buildChildren:
    - Adds transform array support for children (stackY/normalizeY/diffY/map/fold).
    - Embeds function-like strings for encode.x/encode.y.
- src/renderer/init-registry.ts
  - areaSchema accepts data in all common shapes plus arbitrary records.

How to call it (mirroring your example)

- name: generate_area_chart
- arguments:
  {
    "title": "Stacked Area with Line Overlay",
    "data": {
      "type": "fetch",
      "value": "https://gw.alipayobjects.com/os/bmw-prod/f38a8ad0-6e1f-4bb3-894c-7db50781fdec.json"
    },
    "encode": {
      "x": "(d) => new Date(d.year)",
      "y": "revenue",
      "series": "format",
      "color": "group"
    },
    "transform": [
      { "type": "stackY", "orderBy": "maxIndex", "reverse": true }
    ],
    "shape": "smooth",
    "axis": { "y": { "labelFormatter": "~s" } },
    "children": [
      {
        "type": "line",
        "encode": {
          "x": "(d) => new Date(d.year)",
          "y": "revenue",
          "series": "format",
          "shape": "smooth",
          "color": "group"
        },
        "style": { "stroke": "white" },
        "tooltip": false,
        "transform": [
          { "type": "stackY", "orderBy": "maxIndex", "reverse": true, "y": "y1" }
        ]
      }
    ],
    "format": "html-url"
  }

