payload.message:
Done. I added child-level data value/fetch and tooltip function support, and verified it compiles.

What’s new
- Children data:
  - Accepts data: { value: [...] } (array of records for the child mark)
  - Accepts data: { type: 'fetch', value: 'https://...' } for child mark
  - Accepts data: { transform: [...] } for child mark (fold/map) — already supported
- Tooltip functions:
  - Child tooltip can be an object with title (boolean or function-like string) and items as an array of function-like strings; these are embedded as code (not quoted)
  - Child tooltip: false continues to work
- Color/series function-like support:
  - Existing support for function-like strings in encode.x, encode.y, and now encode.color, encode.series where applicable
- Schema updated accordingly:
  - ChildMarkSchema.data supports value/fetch/transform shapes (src/charts/area.ts)

How to use (your example)
- View-level data with map transform:
  - data: { value: data, transform: [{ type: 'map', callback: '(d)=>({ time: d.time, low: d.temperature[0], high: d.temperature[1] })' }] }
- Area band + two overlays using child data values:
  - children:
    - area mark with encode.y = ["low","high"], tooltip with function items
    - line and point marks with child.data.value = averages, function encoders for x

Example payload (html-url)

- name: generate_area_chart
- arguments:
  {
    "title": "Temperature Band with Averages",
    "data": {
      "value": [
        { "time": 1246406400000, "temperature": [14.3, 27.7] },
        { "time": 1246492800000, "temperature": [14.5, 27.8] }
        // ... truncated for brevity ...
      ],
      "transform": [
        {
          "type": "map",
          "callback": "(d) => ({ time: d.time, low: d.temperature[0], high: d.temperature[1] })"
        }
      ]
    },
    "axis": { "y": { "title": false } },
    "children": [
      {
        "type": "area",
        "encode": {
          "x": "(d) => new Date(d.time).toLocaleDateString()",
          "y": ["low", "high"],
          "shape": "area"
        },
        "style": { "fillOpacity": 0.3, "fill": "#64b5f6" },
        "tooltip": {
          "items": ["(d) => ({ name: '温度区间', value: `${d.low}-${d.high}` })"]
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "line",
        "data": { "value": [
          { "time": 1246406400000, "temperature": 21.5 },
          { "time": 1246492800000, "temperature": 22.1 }
          // ... truncated ...
        ]},
        "encode": {
          "x": "(d) => new Date(d.time).toLocaleDateString()",
          "y": "temperature",
          "shape": "line"
        },
        "style": { "lineWidth": 2 },
        "tooltip": {
          "title": false,
          "items": ["(d) => ({ name: '平均温度', value: d.temperature })"]
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "point",
        "data": { "value": [
          { "time": 1246406400000, "temperature": 21.5 },
          { "time": 1246492800000, "temperature": 22.1 }
          // ... truncated ...
        ]},
        "encode": {
          "x": "(d) => new Date(d.time).toLocaleDateString()",
          "y": "temperature",
          "shape": "point",
          "size": 4
        },
        "tooltip": false
      }
    ],
    "format": "html-url"
  }

